Information and communications technology services company iOCO and governance, risk and compliance (GRC) software provider Skywind Software Group have partnered to help clients in Africa in the fight against fraud. Combining iOCO's knowledge of enterprise resource technology company SAP's GRC and the innovative Skywind Analytical Platform for SAP or SkyAPS, iOCO will bring to the African market a cost-effective and efficient governance platform based in the cloud. The platform will provide increased transparency through business process and technical monitoring, managing segregation of duties, violations and performing authorisation inspections. “The partnership with iOCO has created a real synergy based on the vast knowledge and experience of iOCO’s experts, augmented by one of the most innovative monitoring and analytical solutions for SAP, crafted by Skywind. Together we will provide outstanding value for iOCO’s clients in the African market and all over the globe,” says Skywind Software Group co-founder and CEO Iliya Ruvinsky. “Skywind is the perfect partner for us to bring innovation to the GRC domain for our SAP clients. The SkyAPS platform is cloud-based, works on a subscription model and addressing some of the biggest concerns facing organisation in the African context today,” says iOCO enterprise applications head Tshifhiwa Makhari. “Ensuring your organisation’s governance, risk and compliance is running optimally is essential in today’s hyper-connected world. The risks organisations face today are unprecedented. We knew we had to partner with a company that had the innovative products to cater for our clients’ ever-changing needs,” adds iOCO Enterprise Applications COO Elza Kriel.